  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nPart of Epic https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/issues/9816\r\n\r\nThe status-go call `getChats` takes A LOT of time to execute. Even though it is async on the desktop side, it can still cause the DB to lock, which is not great. \r\n\r\nThe reason it is so slow is that it does a lot of actions at once. It gets the chats, members, categories and other infos of all the chat and community sections. Whether or not that section is active.\r\n\r\nMy suggestion would be to split the `getChats` function into a `getChatsBySecitonId`, so we only fetch the data of the currently active section. Therefore, lazy loading the other sections. \r\n\r\nWe still have to load all the sections to get their info to show in the left tab bar however.\r\n\r\nAlso, hopefully status-go can set up the filters for all the chats even if we don't fetch them, we need to double check that. We need to fetch the store nodes for all chats, even if we don't load them in the Nim sections.",
