    "body": "Just some initial stats from the changes I tried. Do note that I don't have the crazy 60 second time Alex got. I tested with my \"main\" account that is part of the Status community, but I did leave the old communities, so it would have a lot longer times if I was. Still, we can see improvements:\r\n\r\n```\r\n# Default\r\n# 0.214520396\r\n# 0.213711711\r\n# 0.215855167\r\n# 0.209258476\r\n\r\n# Without pinned messages\r\n# 0.170445338\r\n# 0.17596633\r\n\r\n# Just chats (no pinned no chat members)\r\n# 0.051695115\r\n# 0.053424918\r\n\r\n# Just sections (no chats)\r\n# 0.022495315\r\n# 0.022023027\r\n```\r\n\r\nSo if we just do an initial `getSections` instead of `getChats`, we get a ~10X improvement.\r\nThen, we'd still need to do `getChatsBySectionId` for the current chat seciton, but still, by not getting the chat members or pinned messages, we save ~4X, plus it would be for only one section, so if you have multiple big sections (communities), you'd save a lot.",
